d'(\theta) = 2R\cos2\theta + 2h\sin2\theta = 0.
v^2
\tan2\theta = -\frac{R}{h},
\sin2\theta = \frac{R}{\sqrt{R^2 +h^2}}, 
 \cos2\theta = \frac{-h}{\sqrt{R^2 +h^2}}.
 v^2  = \frac{gR^2}{R\sin2\theta - h(\cos2\theta+1)}  
 =\frac{gR^2}{\cfrac{R^2}{\sqrt{R^2 +h^2}} +\cfrac{h^2}{\sqrt{R^2 +h^2}} - h} 
= \frac{gR^2}{\sqrt{R^2 + h^2}- h}
= \frac{(gR^2)(\sqrt{R^2 + h^2}+ h)}{(\sqrt{R^2 + h^2} - h)(\sqrt{R^2 + h^2}+h)}
 = g(\sqrt{R^2 + h^2}+ h).
